      <text>
        The evening gathering feels like a trial. Everyone assembles in the common area — Holloway at the center with Elder Twist's pot beside them, Runner coiled tightly, Remedy's edges contracted, Velvet spread thin and watchful; Scout presses against my leg, anxious, and Florence sits alone on the opposite side, her wheeled platform positioned in what feels like an accusatory spotlight.

        The absence of Elder Twist on Florence's back is stark; she looks smaller without the elder, more vulnerable.

        Holloway speaks first.

        [Holloway — controlled, tense]
        Holloway says, "We need to understand the scope of this deception. Florence has admitted that most of Elder Twist's 'wisdom' came from her own thoughts, not the elder. We need to know: how much? How long? What advice was real?"

        [longer beat]
        All the plants say at once, "*YES.*"

        [Holloway — steady]
        Holloway asks, "The dietary guidance when Kira first arrived — when you said Elder Twist counseled patience with unknown nutritional needs. Was that real?"

        [Florence — quiet]
        Florence replies, "No — that was mine. Elder Twist had no opinion on human nutrition."

        [Runner — probing]
        Runner says, "The boundary dispute with Territory Two — last month. You said Elder Twist suggested compromise through shared maintenance."

        [Florence — blunt]
        Florence admits, "Mine."

        [Remedy — precise]
        Remedy says, "The resource allocation plan — the one that prevented the supply shortage —"

        [Florence — interrupted, quick]
        Florence: "Mine."

        [Velvet — simple]
        Velvet asks, "All of it?"

        [Florence — defensive]
        Florence says, "Not ALL. Elder Twist does speak. Sometimes. The fragments are real. But they're… slow. Cryptic. Not immediately helpful. So I expanded them. Made them relevant. Turned wisdom into actionable guidance."

        [Holloway — flat]
        Holloway says, "You mean you made things up."

        [Florence — forceful]
        Florence snaps, "I provided good advice! Look at the outcomes — the dietary guidance helped, the boundary dispute resolved peacefully, we avoided the supply shortage! My counsel was *SOUND.*"

        [Runner — constricting vines, low]
        Runner says, "Your counsel that you falsely attributed to an elder."

        [Florence — rising]
        Florence: "Because you wouldn't have listened otherwise! When would any of you have valued *my* tactical judgment? Florence the mobile platform, Florence who can't even stay upright on rough terrain, Florence who needs help for everything? But Elder Twist — ah, Elder Twist commands respect. Elder Twist is ancient and wise. So I gave you wisdom you'd actually hear."

        The accusation sits heavy in the room.

        [Holloway — uncertain]
        Holloway says, "That's not fair."

        [Florence — challenging]
        Florence asks, "Isn't it? Tell me honestly — if I had offered those same suggestions as *my* thoughts, would you have taken them as seriously?"

        ¶

        Silence.

        [Florence — bitter]
        Florence says, "Exactly. I knew what needed to be done. I had good instincts. But good instincts from Florence weren't enough. They needed to come from someone who mattered."

        [me — soft]
        I say, "You matter."

        [Florence — swivel, sharp]
        Florence's platform swivels toward me. Florence asks, "Do I? Or am I just the one who carries the elder who matters?"
      </text>
