        Holloway interrupts — "You're deflecting. This isn't about whether we valued you enough. This is about you lying to us — repeatedly. For how long, Florence? When did this start?"

        Florence doesn't answer immediately.

        Remedy says — slowly, making connections — "When Kira arrived the first 'Elder Twist' guidance about human care. That was weeks ago. You've been doing this for weeks."

        Florence admits — "Longer. The fabrications started before Kira. I just refined the technique with her arrival more crises, more need for guidance, more opportunities to be useful."

        Runner says — "Useful through deception."

        Florence counters — *"Useful DESPITE limitations."* "I can't move fast like Scout. I can't reach everywhere like Runner's underground networks. I can't process information like Remedy's distributed cognition. I can't maintain growth like Velvet. I'm slow immobile without wheels dependent on others for basic tasks. But I can THINK. I can analyze situations and provide sound tactical advice. Carrying Elder Twist gave me value—or I thought it did. Until I realized the value was the elder, not me."

        There's pain in Florence's voice now real pain, not just defensiveness.

        Holloway says — "So you created false value. Pretended Elder Twist's authority was yours."

        Florence corrects — wheeling slightly, agitated — "I created REAL value using borrowed authority. The advice helped! The outcomes were good! Does the source actually matter if the guidance works?"

        Holloway says firmly — "Yes. The source matters. Trust requires honesty. You violated that."

        Florence argues — "We just spent the last week learning that authority doesn't actually have better answers! Elder Heartwood failed us. The H R manuals failed. We learned to trust our own judgment instead of waiting for wisdom from above. And now you're angry that I what, proved that point first? Showed you that wisdom doesn't require authority?"

        Remedy says quietly — "That's not what you did. You didn't show us wisdom without authority. You created false authority to hide behind."

        Florence — wheeling back and forth, voice rising — "Because true authority failed! The first human died because you had no framework. You found the H R manuals and they didn't work. You consulted Elder Heartwood and got irrelevant ecosystem philosophy. Every authority you turned to FAILED. But my guidance—my fabricated, unauthorized guidance—actually helped!"

        Runner repeats — "While lying to us."

        Florence shouts — *"I was TRYING TO HELP!*"

        ¶

        Florence says — quieter now — "I was trying to help. I saw what needed to be done. I knew how to solve the problems. But I didn't trust that you'd listen to me, so I gave you something you would listen to — an elder's voice. And it worked. Everything I advised it worked!"

        Velvet says simply — "It's still lying."

        Florence makes a sound like breaking wood.
      </text>
