        - Treat the line "I was TRYING TO HELP!" as a loud, desperate explosion — bold and forceful; then drop immediately into a long silence (the paragraph with only "¶").
        - After the silence, soften to a quieter, pleading tone for "I was trying to help..." and keep the following sentences measured but earnest.
        - For Velvet's line, deliver it flat, direct, and devastating — no flourish.
        - End the chunk with the almost-sonic, physical cue: "Florence makes a sound like breaking wood." — read as an observation, not dialogue.
      </stage-directions>
